# Yesanio does not currently use a .env file. Credentials are hardcoded
# in docker-compose.yml. This file exists as a placeholder for future
# use (SMTP config, API keys, etc.) and to document the convention.
#
# If you fork Yesanio and add secrets, put them here and add .env to
# your .gitignore. Leave this .env.example committed as documentation.
